model.haskell_template:
import Control.Applicative
import Control.Monad
import System.IO


main :: IO ()
main = do
    q_temp <- getLine
    let q = read q_temp :: Int
    forM_ [1..q] $ \a0  -> do
        x_temp <- getLine
        let x_t = words x_temp
        let x = read $ x_t!!0 :: Int
        let y = read $ x_t!!1 :: Int
        let z = read $ x_t!!2 :: Int


getMultipleLines :: Int -> IO [String]

getMultipleLines n
    | n <= 0 = return []
    | otherwise = do          
        x <- getLine         
        xs <- getMultipleLines (n-1)    
        let ret = (x:xs)    
        return ret
model.preview: Which cat will catch the mouse first?
model.clojure_template:
(use '[clojure.string :only (split triml)])

(
        let [
          q_t (read-line) 
          q (Integer/parseInt q_t) 
        ]

      (
        loop [a0 q]
        (when (> a0 0)

          (
            let [
              x_temp (read-line) 
              x_t (split x_temp #"\s+") 
              x (Integer/parseInt (x_t 0)) 
              y (Integer/parseInt (x_t 1)) 
              z (Integer/parseInt (x_t 2)) 
            ]
          )

        (recur (- a0 1) ) )
      )

)

read_array(0,D) -> [];
read_array(N,D) ->

	[X | read_array(N-1,D)].
